Preconditions:
- The input array `stones` is not null.
- The length of the input array `stones` is at least 3.
- All the values in the input array `stones` are unique.
- The values in the input array `stones` are within the range of 1 to 10^9.

Postconditions:
- The output array `answer` is not null.
- The length of the output array `answer` is 2.
- The first element of the output array `answer[0]` represents the minimum number of moves to finish the game.
- The second element of the output array `answer[1]` represents the maximum number of moves to finish the game.
- The values in the output array `answer` are within the range of 0 to the length of the input array `stones` minus 3.